# .dockerignore for the content-baked db image build.
#
# Resolved against the build context (db/) — the directory passed to
# `docker build`. Docker looks for `.dockerignore` in the build context
# root and recursively upward, so this file's location depends on where
# the build is launched from, not on this file's name. We launch
# `docker build db/` from the project root, so this file is the one
# docker reads.
#
# Rules are matched as Go-style filepath patterns:
#   `/audio`  — anchored to the context root: matches `audio/` only
#               at the top level of the context, NOT anywhere deeper.
#   `foo`     — matches `foo` anywhere in the context (recursive).
#
# We add `/audio` as a guard rail: if someone ever changes the build
# context to `cms/` itself (instead of `db/`), this rule keeps the
# persistent CMS working directory `cms/.local/audio` out of the image.
# Today the build context is `db/`, which has no top-level `audio/`,
# so the rule is a no-op — but it documents intent and prevents future
# surprise. (Audio itself now lives in Tencent Cloud COS, not in this
# build context — see cms/cms_pipeline/storage.py.)
/audio
